JOHANNESBURG - Diepsloot residents are threatening to block the route that Winnie Madikizela-Mandela's funeral procession will take. They are upset over a stalled project in the area and are demanding that workers be paid. READ: Motorists urged to avoid roads around Orlando Stadium The struggle icon will be buried on Saturday in Fourways, but her funeral service will be held in Orlando Stadium in Soweto, with thousands expected to attend. Government will outline the logistics on Friday. OBITUARY: The incredible life of Winnie Madikizela-Mandela Tributes have been pouring from around the globe for the icon. Meanwhile, eNCA will re-broadcast a documentary on Winnie Madikizela-Mandela on Friday at 9pm, Saturday at 4pm and Sunday at 8pm. eNCA